"<a href="#"><img alt="P1" src="https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/p1.svg?v=7" align="top"></a> **Unescaped `&` in search query or `from_user` name breaks URL**

`sanitized` removes only double-quotes, but leaves through URL special characters. A search for `"Q&A"` produces `?$search="Q&A"&$top=25`, and HTTP clients (including `reqwest`) treat the bare `&` as a query-string separator — `$search` receives only `"Q` and the search fails silently.

The same issue applies to the `$filter` append when `from_user` contains `&`.

Use `reqwest`'s `.query()` builder to let the library handle encoding:

```rust
let search_val = format!("\"{}\"", sanitized);
let mut query_params: Vec<(&str, String)> = vec![
    ("$search", search_val.clone()),
    ("$top", top.to_string()),
];
if let Some(user) = from_user {
    query_params.push(("$filter",
        format!("from/user/displayName eq '{}'", user.replace('\'', "''"))));
}
let resp = http
    .get(format!("{GRAPH_API_BASE}/chats/{}/messages", urlencoding::encode(chat_id)))
    .query(&query_params)
    .bearer_auth(token.expose_secret())
    .header("ConsistencyLevel", "eventual")
    .send()
    .await?;
```"

